# Chlorine Dosing Rotometer Simulator
**Author:** Joshua Brunner  
**Date:** 2026-05-04  
**Repository:** github.com/Papaperun/OT-Quest

---

## Overview

A Python/pygame simulation of a chlorine dosing rotometer used in municipal water treatment. Built from operational experience as a Class A Water Treatment Operator with 22+ years in municipal water systems.

This is not a generic PLC demo. Every parameter in this simulator reflects real world water treatment operational limits.

---

## What It Simulates

A rotometer is a flow measurement device used to monitor chemical feed rates in water treatment. This simulator models a chlorine dosing rotometer scaled to:

- **Flow range:** 0–24 MGD (Million Gallons Per Day)
- **Signal range:** 4–20mA (industry standard analog signal) # not yet wired in 
- **Dosage range:** 0–10 mg/L (realistic for a pure water source)
- **Output range:** 0–800 lbs/day chlorine demand

---

## The Math

```
lbs/day = Flow (MGD) × 8.34 (lbs/gallon) × Dosage (mg/L)
```

This is the standard water treatment dosing formula. The 8.34 conversion factor is the weight of one gallon of water in pounds.

**4-20mA scaling:**
```
mA = ((flow / 24) * 16) + 4
```
- 0 MGD = 4mA
- 24 MGD = 20mA

---

## Controls

| Key | Action |
|-----|--------|
| W | Increase flow +1 MGD |
| S | Decrease flow -1 MGD |
| D | Increase dosage +1 mg/L |
| A | Decrease dosage -1 mg/L |

---

## Features

- Input validation — rejects values outside operational boundaries before entering the system
- Live display — flow, dosage, and lbs/day update in real time
- Ball position tracks dosage output scaled 0–800 lbs/day
- Physical limits — ball cannot exceed sight glass boundaries
- Real water treatment parameters throughout

---

## Security Relevance

This simulator represents the **HMI/display layer** of a chemical dosing system. The input validation built into the user interface is intentionally bypassed when values are written directly to process registers over Modbus TCP.

A Modbus write to the flow or dosage register:
- Skips all input validation
- Accepts any value regardless of operational boundaries
- Updates the display and recalculates output immediately
- Generates no authentication challenge

This demonstrates **MITRE ATT&CK for ICS T0836 — Modify Parameter** at the process level.

Phase 2 of this project will expose these registers over unauthenticated Modbus TCP to demonstrate the attack surface. This simulator becomes the target.

---

## Why This Exists

Built as part of a broader OT security lab (OT-Quest) to demonstrate that ICS vulnerabilities are not abstract — they live in the same systems that treat drinking water for real communities.

The rotometer is dead simple. The implications are not.

